<h2><a id="FocalPlane" name="FocalPlane"></a>The Company of Biologists and Journal of Cell Science launch FocalPlane, a new microscopy community site</h2>
<p><a href="https://focalplane.biologists.com/" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/ImageLibrary/JournalsGateway/FocalPlane-logo.png?versionId=6776" style="width: 200px; height: 59px;" /></a></p>
<p>FocalPlane is the third community site launched by The Company of Biologists, following in the successful footsteps of the Node and preLights.</p>
<p>For anyone with an interest in microscopy, FocalPlane will host news, interviews, opinions, images, tools, job listings and events to help promote interactions and foster connections. The site is free to access and users can register for a free account to post their own contribution.</p>
<p>A Scientific Advisory Board has been appointed to support the site alongside its own dedicated Community Manager.</p>
<p>“We encourage you to make the site part of your online routine, and look forward to many interactions with you all,” says Sharon Ahmad, Executive Editor, Journal of Cell Science.</p>
