<h2><a id="preLights" name="preLights"></a>preLights goes live</h2>
<p><img alt="" src="https://cob.silverchair-cdn.com/ImageLibrary/JournalsGateway/preLights_logo_RGB.png?versionId=6776" style="width: 200px; height: 70px;" /></p>
<p>The Company of Biologists, the publisher of Journal of Experimental Biology, has launched preLights, a new preprint highlights service, run by the biological community.</p>
<p>preLights has a dedicated team of scientists from the community who regularly select, highlight and comment on preprints they feel are of interest to the biological community. You’ll find a summary of each preprint, the reasons it was selected and the selector’s thoughts on its significance. You might also see relevant comments from the preprints’ authors and we strongly encourage website visitors to join in the conversation.</p>
<p>For the latest posts and more information visit <a href="https://prelights.biologists.com/">https://prelights.biologists.com</a>.</p>
<p><em>20 February 2018</em></p>
